- There is no longer a delay between what commands your pet hears.<br>
- Pet commands can be heard anywhere in the zone.<br>
<br>
For this reason, I now have changed my hotkeys.<br>
My pet attack hotkey now has this:<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
This one hotkey makes my pet attack my target, usually no matter what he is doing.  It also lets him switch targets easily.<br>
<br>
I still have a /pet back off hotkey, but when I get /pet hold, it will just be a /pet hold hotkey.  If you have /pet hold, you only need 2 hotkeys now, instead of 3. Just do what I listed here and you should be good to go. <p><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" align="center"><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710">My Character Profile</a>
