<br>
Actually the workaround I use for the /pet attack command is to issue a /pet guard me command, the pet will come running from anywhere in the zone, and once it hits the aggro radius (which is very large when the mage is getting beat on), it will take the mob.<br>
<br>
A good example of using this would be DS Peaks, I'd park my pet by the Neth zone line, and head out and pull zelniaks, if a wolf would add, I'd use pet guard me followed by pet attack to take down the wolf. This strategy didn't work nearly as well in Stonebrunt near the kitty city, as pathing is pretty bad on the mountain side.....<br>
<br>
