<br>
What Hogfather was asking, was very simple and would of been correct.<br>
<br>
If Mob a is 20 feet in front of you, Mob b, c, d and e are 2 rooms away.  You send pet to attack mob a, pet paths through b c d and e after he casts on mob a, and you could be looking at adds.<br>
<br>
If pet didn't cast on mob a before pathing through b c d and e then you shouldn't see any adds.  <br>
<br>
Alot of this would have to do with at what point did mob a give a call for help.  Did the call for help occur right as pet was leaving sight of mob a and entering site of b c d and e?  If that were the case then yes you would be looking at adds.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, this is all mute.  You and hogfather both missed an important statement.  If it pathed through b c d and e, then I doubt it would of made it back to a.  I am sure that if by some chance the call for help came as pet was leaving site of 1 and entering site of the other 4, then pet would of stopped the second the other 4 started beating on him.  Conseder that, and pet would of never made it to mob a (unless pet dispatched the other 4 first....alone....).<br>
<br>
My guess on what happened:  Puller pulled mob a, was running along and targeted b (cause he wanted to know what mob was overthere because he couldn't make out what it was).  Mage then hit assist and sent pet off to attack mob b, which was where c d and e were, then pet saw mob a was low on health and came down to assist with it.  <br>
<br>
This is the only practicle explanation, as the chances of the call for help coming at the precise time pet was leaving sight of 1 and entering the sight of another would be extremely slim.  The higher probability has to be the puller targeted a mob that he wasn't pulling, thus causing the train.  <br>
<br>
My understanding of how a call for help might be wrong, but as I understand it:  When mob calls for help it creates an agro radius around itself of which any social mob in that radius will assist.  It also creates an agro radius around it's attacker (those currently on it's hate list), of which any social mob that comes into either circle will assist.<br>
<br>
rhionsligo, hogfathers attempt at an explanation for this according to my understanding of a call for help would of been correct.  Furthermore, his statement about betting the pet proc'ed cast or otherwise attacked the pull WAS a valid question.  That would of added pet to the hate list and involved the pet in the call for help.  <br>
<br>
Another possibility, pet might of taunted while running past the other mobs, which I cannot say for sure, but would only make sence if other social mobs saw that as a hostile act, and hence agro'ed.  In this, the mage should of had the sence to turn pet taunt off, which is customary practice anyplace where there is bad pathing or unknown pathing (meaning first time I enter a zone, I turn pet taunts off until I see how well the pet acts).<br>
<br>
Another thing the mage could of done and prevented what happened, would of been to change his view so he could see his pet.  Once /pet attack was issued, if he saw pet take 1 step in the wrong direction he should of been slamming /pet back off.  Hey I may not care if the pet runs past 40 social mobs, but I sure as hell don't want the pet to take a 10 minute tour of the zone to get to a mob 20 feet in front of me.  It's just as easy to hit /pet back off and move a little so that pet will take a more direct route, than it is to wait for 5 minutes while your pet goes exploring. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urhionsligo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 655<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/02 3:38:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=532.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet hotkey tips! *NEW!*</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I am sure that if by some chance the call for help came as pet was leaving site of 1 and entering site of the other 4, then pet would of stopped the second the other 4 started beating on him.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
